1
00:01:02,020 --> 00:01:03,480
She's here.

2
00:01:03,564 --> 00:01:04,398
Ms. Kim Hye-joo.

3
00:01:04,481 --> 00:01:06,567
Did you really kill someone 20 years ago?

4
00:01:06,650 --> 00:01:08,110
-Tell us!
-Please answer us.

5
00:01:08,193 --> 00:01:10,487
-Is this true?
-Were you involved in someone's death?

6
00:01:12,072 --> 00:01:13,365
<i><font color="white">Kim Jae-eun.</font></i>

7
00:01:13,991 --> 00:01:14,950
Yes?

8
00:01:19,454 --> 00:01:20,998
You killed him. You murderer.

9
00:01:21,081 --> 00:01:24,334
Get out of here.
How dare you show up here?

10
00:01:24,418 --> 00:01:27,379
Get out. Get out of here now!

11
00:01:27,462 --> 00:01:29,631
My child died because of you.

12
00:01:34,219 --> 00:01:35,429
<i><font color="white">Murderer.</font></i>

13
00:01:59,328 --> 00:02:01,163
THE NIGHTMARE

14
00:02:23,685 --> 00:02:25,771
CLEAN, HONEST, AND COMPETENT WORKER
NAM JOONG-DO

15
00:02:28,148 --> 00:02:28,982
Goodness.

16
00:02:29,566 --> 00:02:31,234
-Hello.
-Hi, Ms. Kim.

17
00:02:35,530 --> 00:02:37,074
-Go ahead and order.
-Okay.

18
00:02:37,157 --> 00:02:39,534
-Thank you, ma'am.
-You're welcome.

19
00:02:39,618 --> 00:02:41,662
We'll have six cups
of hot americano to go.

20
00:02:41,745 --> 00:02:43,288
Okay, six cups of americano.

21
00:02:43,372 --> 00:02:46,083
Can you change one of them
to a non-coffee drink?

22
00:02:46,667 --> 00:02:48,377
My husband doesn't drink coffee.

23
00:02:48,460 --> 00:02:51,755
He actually does these days.

24
00:02:52,422 --> 00:02:54,216
Really?

25
00:02:54,299 --> 00:02:55,592
Then forget about that.

26
00:02:55,675 --> 00:02:58,220
No. Please change one of them to tea.

27
00:02:58,303 --> 00:03:00,430
-Five coffees and one tea.
-Sure.

28
00:03:04,976 --> 00:03:06,686
So what we were doing was…

29
00:03:06,770 --> 00:03:08,980
You know the mill lady, right?

30
00:03:09,064 --> 00:03:10,273
Of course you do.

31
00:03:10,357 --> 00:03:12,567
We were just visiting her
regarding the bill.

32
00:03:12,651 --> 00:03:14,694
Assemblyman Nam is
coming to the district office

33
00:03:14,778 --> 00:03:17,155
after attending the hearing
at the Sinyang-gu office.

34
00:03:18,740 --> 00:03:19,658
I see.

35
00:03:24,579 --> 00:03:25,414
And…

36
00:03:26,540 --> 00:03:27,874
Things must have been hard for you.

37
00:03:28,959 --> 00:03:29,918
Sorry?

38
00:03:30,544 --> 00:03:31,795
Right.

39
00:03:31,878 --> 00:03:33,463
About that…

40
00:03:34,047 --> 00:03:37,926
I never got to thank you
for helping out with my son's funeral.

41
00:03:38,009 --> 00:03:38,969
Thank you so much.

42
00:03:39,553 --> 00:03:42,514
No, Ms. Kim. I was talking
about the incident in Youngsan.

43
00:03:44,558 --> 00:03:45,976
The suicide.

44
00:03:48,937 --> 00:03:49,855
Right.

45
00:03:50,439 --> 00:03:52,983
Thank you for making such a big decision.

46
00:03:54,151 --> 00:03:57,112
Senior Secretary Kim Bit-na

47
00:03:57,195 --> 00:04:00,574
spent all afternoon yesterday
writing up your statement.

48
00:04:00,657 --> 00:04:03,827
She really put her heart and soul into it.

49
00:04:05,120 --> 00:04:06,371
I see. Thank you.

50
00:04:09,416 --> 00:04:11,793
Wait, did you say yesterday afternoon?

51
00:04:12,377 --> 00:04:13,378
Yes.

52
00:04:13,462 --> 00:04:14,755
Yesterday afternoon.

53
00:04:15,338 --> 00:04:19,301
Let's disclose it
before Assemblyman Kang does.

54
00:04:22,596 --> 00:04:25,223
Will Ms. Kim be okay with that?

55
00:04:25,974 --> 00:04:27,434
This will cause a huge stir.

56
00:04:28,185 --> 00:04:30,437
She had seen this coming
and previously agreed.

57
00:04:31,354 --> 00:04:33,148
We've just been waiting
for the right time.

58
00:04:34,691 --> 00:04:36,234
Please write up a statement.

59
00:04:40,113 --> 00:04:41,656
<i><font color="white">I won't publicize your story</font></i>

60
00:04:42,657 --> 00:04:45,076
until you give your consent.

61
00:04:50,791 --> 00:04:53,335
We will do our absolute best.

62
00:04:53,418 --> 00:04:55,545
Yes. We'll work hard.

63
00:04:57,088 --> 00:04:58,089
Thank you.

64
00:05:00,801 --> 00:05:02,093
Honey.

65
00:05:02,177 --> 00:05:03,845
-Hello, sir.
-Hello.

66
00:05:04,763 --> 00:05:06,348
I heard you were here.

67
00:05:09,518 --> 00:05:10,936
I'll bring the drinks.

68
00:05:11,603 --> 00:05:13,146
Let me help you.

69
00:05:14,648 --> 00:05:16,024
Were you out buying paper?

70
00:05:16,858 --> 00:05:17,901
Yes.

71
00:05:21,905 --> 00:05:23,907
-Honey.
-Yes?

72
00:05:25,242 --> 00:05:27,661
They just told me something.

73
00:05:27,744 --> 00:05:30,747
The decision to disclose
the Youngsan incident…

74
00:05:32,040 --> 00:05:34,876
Did you already make up your mind
yesterday afternoon

75
00:05:34,960 --> 00:05:36,920
before asking me about it last night?

76
00:05:42,884 --> 00:05:44,678
Is that true?

77
00:05:48,598 --> 00:05:49,558
Yes, it is.

78
00:05:56,815 --> 00:05:58,316
You two go ahead.

79
00:05:58,400 --> 00:06:00,318
-I'll stay here for a bit.
-Okay.

80
00:06:00,402 --> 00:06:01,486
Thank you for the drinks.

81
00:06:01,570 --> 00:06:04,823
Right. Here's your tea, sir.

82
00:06:04,906 --> 00:06:06,032
Thank you.

83
00:06:06,616 --> 00:06:07,576
We'll be going then.

84
00:06:20,463 --> 00:06:21,798
I'll be honest.

85
00:06:22,591 --> 00:06:23,550
It's true.

86
00:06:24,175 --> 00:06:25,802
I had already made up my mind.

87
00:06:28,638 --> 00:06:30,056
Like I told you yesterday,

88
00:06:30,140 --> 00:06:32,517
Assemblyman Kang agreed
to keep it a secret,

89
00:06:33,602 --> 00:06:36,813
but it's a matter of time
before Ms. Jin or her mother discloses it.

90
00:06:38,106 --> 00:06:40,734
Even if you're innocent,

91
00:06:41,234 --> 00:06:43,194
you'll still be dragged through the mud.

92
00:06:44,195 --> 00:06:47,616
That's why I wanted to get a head start.

93
00:06:48,867 --> 00:06:52,329
We were just preparing in advance.
That's all.

94
00:06:59,377 --> 00:07:00,587
"That's all"?

95
00:07:02,255 --> 00:07:04,507
How could you say that?

96
00:07:04,591 --> 00:07:06,801
You should've asked me first.

97
00:07:06,885 --> 00:07:08,178
I did ask you.

98
00:07:08,261 --> 00:07:11,056
Sure, but it was after you had
already made up your mind.

99
00:07:11,640 --> 00:07:13,016
If it was already decided,

100
00:07:13,767 --> 00:07:16,311
why did you even bother
to ask for my permission?

101
00:07:19,648 --> 00:07:21,107
What if I said no?

102
00:07:22,984 --> 00:07:25,320
Would you have still gone through with it?

103
00:07:25,403 --> 00:07:26,488
No.

104
00:07:27,822 --> 00:07:29,658
I could have if I had wanted to,

105
00:07:30,825 --> 00:07:33,954
but I asked you because I respect you.

106
00:07:36,414 --> 00:07:38,833
I thought you were going
to give me your permission.

107
00:07:51,346 --> 00:07:53,598
I don't even know what to say right now.

108
00:07:55,600 --> 00:07:59,270
Do you even know
how difficult it was for me

109
00:08:00,397 --> 00:08:03,066
to make that decision yesterday?

110
00:08:05,318 --> 00:08:06,194
I'm sorry.

111
00:08:07,404 --> 00:08:08,488
It was wrong of me.

112
00:08:09,781 --> 00:08:13,243
I don't know when they'd make a move,
so I wanted to be ready.

113
00:08:15,704 --> 00:08:16,913
And I got ahead of myself.

114
00:08:17,747 --> 00:08:18,748
I'm sorry.

115
00:08:56,119 --> 00:08:57,579
Hello, sir.

116
00:08:57,662 --> 00:08:59,748
-Hello.
-Hello.

117
00:08:59,831 --> 00:09:01,416
-Hello, sir.
-Hello.

118
00:09:01,499 --> 00:09:05,420
You're glowing after being on a date.

119
00:09:06,129 --> 00:09:07,297
Does it show?

120
00:09:09,007 --> 00:09:11,551
I have a tight schedule today.
Shall we begin?

121
00:09:11,634 --> 00:09:13,219
-Yes, sir.
-Yes, sir.

122
00:09:13,303 --> 00:09:15,472
Sir, would you like some tea?

123
00:09:15,555 --> 00:09:17,390
I'll have a cup of coffee, please.

124
00:09:31,529 --> 00:09:32,822
What?

125
00:09:32,906 --> 00:09:34,282
What did you say, Soon-hong?

126
00:09:34,365 --> 00:09:36,451
He mentioned Mr. Park?

127
00:09:36,534 --> 00:09:38,578
I'm telling you.

128
00:09:39,329 --> 00:09:42,165
Mr. Park of Yangcheon-ri, Youngsan,
is great at his job.

129
00:09:44,459 --> 00:09:46,586
How does he know him?

130
00:09:46,669 --> 00:09:48,838
How would I know that?

131
00:09:49,964 --> 00:09:50,965
What should we do?

132
00:09:52,217 --> 00:09:55,512
I'll take care of this,

133
00:09:55,595 --> 00:09:58,056
so you should lie low.

134
00:09:58,139 --> 00:09:59,974
Lying low won't resolve this.

135
00:10:00,058 --> 00:10:02,977
What if we end up in big trouble?

136
00:10:03,061 --> 00:10:05,355
<i><font color="white">If this blows up,</font></i>

137
00:10:05,438 --> 00:10:08,942
I'll be the one
in the biggest trouble, not you.

138
00:10:09,025 --> 00:10:10,985
The general election is around the corner.

139
00:10:11,069 --> 00:10:12,987
I'll be in trouble too.

140
00:10:13,571 --> 00:10:15,698
I trusted that you'd take care of this,

141
00:10:15,782 --> 00:10:17,867
but you're telling me
that he knows Mr. Park.

142
00:10:17,951 --> 00:10:21,538
<i><font color="white">Then we should meet up
and come up with a plan.</font></i>

143
00:10:22,038 --> 00:10:25,583
How are you going to keep
that assemblyman's mouth shut?

144
00:10:25,667 --> 00:10:29,045
Just stay out of it!
You don't know anything.

145
00:10:30,421 --> 00:10:32,382
Don't you know

146
00:10:32,966 --> 00:10:36,469
that Nam Joong-do's wife
was the one who killed Seung-ho?

147
00:10:38,304 --> 00:10:39,347
Soon-hong.

148
00:10:40,140 --> 00:10:41,266
What did you--

149
00:10:41,349 --> 00:10:43,226
<i><font color="white">Nam Joong-do's wife is the one</font></i>

150
00:10:43,309 --> 00:10:46,729
who's responsible for Seung-ho's death.

151
00:10:49,399 --> 00:10:50,608
Do you mean

152
00:10:51,484 --> 00:10:52,735
Kim Jae-eun?

153
00:11:54,380 --> 00:11:56,257
Hello, is this Ji-hoon's uncle?

154
00:11:56,341 --> 00:11:58,051
I'm Ji-hoon's…

155
00:12:01,846 --> 00:12:02,847
Yes.

156
00:12:03,556 --> 00:12:04,682
Have you been well?

157
00:12:04,766 --> 00:12:06,351
Is your mother doing well?

158
00:12:09,646 --> 00:12:12,315
I'd like to send you a parcel,

159
00:12:12,398 --> 00:12:16,945
and I want to make sure
I have the right address.

160
00:12:19,155 --> 00:12:21,282
JICHEONG-DONG POST OFFICE

161
00:12:51,437 --> 00:12:53,022
He went to the Seoul headquarters?

162
00:12:53,106 --> 00:12:54,315
Yes.

163
00:12:54,399 --> 00:12:55,942
Were you supposed to meet him?

164
00:12:56,025 --> 00:12:59,028
No, I just stopped by.

165
00:12:59,612 --> 00:13:00,822
We filled out the form.

166
00:13:00,905 --> 00:13:02,824
One minute, please.

167
00:13:02,907 --> 00:13:04,200
Thank you.

168
00:13:04,283 --> 00:13:06,786
Then let me introduce our facilities.

169
00:13:06,869 --> 00:13:07,996
This way, please.

170
00:13:08,871 --> 00:13:11,916
Hello, I'm interested
in taking some golf lessons.

171
00:13:12,000 --> 00:13:13,376
I see.

172
00:13:13,459 --> 00:13:16,170
Then let me show them around.

173
00:13:16,254 --> 00:13:17,380
-This way.
-Let's go.

174
00:13:17,463 --> 00:13:18,798
Let's go.

175
00:13:22,301 --> 00:13:26,556
Our system lets you
immediately monitor your swings.

176
00:13:26,639 --> 00:13:29,017
You can also practice putting
in an environment

177
00:13:29,100 --> 00:13:30,768
similar to a real golf course.

178
00:13:30,852 --> 00:13:33,646
We have plenty of slots
so you can come in anytime

179
00:13:33,730 --> 00:13:35,606
for practice or lessons.

180
00:13:53,750 --> 00:13:54,751
Hey, Ki-young.

181
00:13:54,834 --> 00:13:55,793
Hey, Hye-joo.

182
00:13:56,377 --> 00:13:57,545
Have you been well?

183
00:13:57,628 --> 00:13:59,881
I'm on my way to Seoul.

184
00:14:01,090 --> 00:14:02,050
Can you make

185
00:14:03,301 --> 00:14:04,886
some time for me?

186
00:14:04,969 --> 00:14:06,220
Right now?

187
00:14:08,765 --> 00:14:10,099
Sure.

188
00:14:18,900 --> 00:14:21,277
I'm off to the district office.

189
00:14:23,029 --> 00:14:24,614
You're meeting Mr. Choi there, right?

190
00:14:25,948 --> 00:14:26,908
Yes.

191
00:14:27,575 --> 00:14:30,119
If we meet here,
Assemblyman Kang might see us.

192
00:14:30,870 --> 00:14:31,871
Right.

193
00:14:35,917 --> 00:14:36,959
You know,

194
00:14:37,835 --> 00:14:39,128
to be honest.

195
00:14:39,212 --> 00:14:42,590
I'm a bit concerned about Mr. Choi.

196
00:14:43,424 --> 00:14:44,300
Why?

197
00:14:44,384 --> 00:14:46,219
He's definitely doing the right thing

198
00:14:46,302 --> 00:14:48,763
by handing us the evidence
for the land speculation.

199
00:14:49,889 --> 00:14:54,143
But in a way, he's betraying
his wife and her family.

200
00:14:54,227 --> 00:14:56,687
Think about it.
Once Ms. Jin finds out about this,

201
00:14:57,313 --> 00:14:58,898
she'll feel extremely betrayed.

202
00:14:59,982 --> 00:15:02,777
Seeing how Mr. Choi asked us
to keep this a secret,

203
00:15:02,860 --> 00:15:04,779
I don't think he wants a divorce.

204
00:15:04,862 --> 00:15:08,366
If I imagine this happened
between me and my husband,

205
00:15:08,449 --> 00:15:11,911
I would feel uneasy about it
even if it's the right thing to do.

206
00:15:13,413 --> 00:15:17,417
There's no perfect secret
that can be kept forever.

207
00:15:19,627 --> 00:15:20,503
I'm sure there is.

208
00:15:21,921 --> 00:15:22,922
Sorry?

209
00:15:24,340 --> 00:15:27,760
This "perfect secret"
you're talking about.

210
00:15:30,012 --> 00:15:31,013
I'm sure there is one.

211
00:15:31,097 --> 00:15:32,223
Of course.

212
00:15:32,306 --> 00:15:36,394
We'll keep Mr. Choi's secret at all costs.

213
00:15:38,104 --> 00:15:39,105
Right.

214
00:15:40,064 --> 00:15:41,649
-I'll be off then.
-Okay.

215
00:15:41,732 --> 00:15:42,817
See you later.

216
00:15:52,910 --> 00:15:54,162
I'm sorry.

217
00:15:57,165 --> 00:15:58,541
About Seung-ho…

218
00:16:00,710 --> 00:16:02,628
Could you apologize to them?

219
00:16:05,756 --> 00:16:07,508
You may not have done anything wrong,

220
00:16:07,592 --> 00:16:11,721
but you understand the pain
of losing a family member.

221
00:16:13,890 --> 00:16:16,559
I realized what I said that day

222
00:16:17,059 --> 00:16:18,728
must have hurt you deeply.

223
00:16:19,812 --> 00:16:20,646
I'm sorry.

224
00:16:24,192 --> 00:16:27,028
Seung-hee means so much to me,

225
00:16:28,196 --> 00:16:29,906
and I was being emotional.

226
00:16:33,326 --> 00:16:35,536
I actually only decided
to help your husband

227
00:16:36,370 --> 00:16:37,705
for her sake.

228
00:16:39,165 --> 00:16:40,416
I want her

229
00:16:41,250 --> 00:16:44,462
to see her mother for who she truly is.

230
00:16:46,589 --> 00:16:48,549
I think it would be best for her.

231
00:16:49,842 --> 00:16:51,344
That's why I decided to do this.

232
00:16:56,516 --> 00:17:00,561
But wouldn't she feel hurt
if she ever finds out?

233
00:17:03,314 --> 00:17:04,148
Probably.

234
00:17:06,067 --> 00:17:08,986
But I had no choice.

235
