526
00:36:24,474 --> 00:36:25,934
I need two million won.

527
00:36:26,518 --> 00:36:28,019
Tell me your account number.

528
00:36:28,603 --> 00:36:30,105
TRANSACTIONS
2,500,000 WON

529
00:36:30,188 --> 00:36:32,357
2,500,000 WON, NARA BANK

530
00:36:34,734 --> 00:36:39,531
BACK

531
00:36:40,407 --> 00:36:41,449
What's going on?

532
00:36:44,536 --> 00:36:47,247
Why would I give you money
when you crashed into my car?

533
00:36:47,330 --> 00:36:48,498
Do you not want to?

534
00:36:49,499 --> 00:36:51,918
Should I call in some reporters then?

535
00:36:52,502 --> 00:36:54,629
And tell them about your call girls?

536
00:36:58,007 --> 00:36:58,842
Fine.

537
00:36:59,718 --> 00:37:01,970
-Give me your account number.
-Now we're talking.

538
00:37:04,681 --> 00:37:06,599
-Kim Soo-bin.
-What?

539
00:37:09,853 --> 00:37:11,229
Have it wired to your account.

540
00:37:11,938 --> 00:37:13,523
-To mine?
-Yes.

541
00:37:13,606 --> 00:37:15,525
-Cheers!
-Drink up!

542
00:37:15,608 --> 00:37:17,944
Hey, careful.

543
00:37:18,027 --> 00:37:19,320
You're spilling it.

544
00:37:19,404 --> 00:37:21,573
Soo-bin, give me your debit card.

545
00:37:22,490 --> 00:37:24,409
-My card?
-Yes.

546
00:37:24,492 --> 00:37:26,119
I want to withdraw the cash.

547
00:37:29,581 --> 00:37:30,957
Someone's been busy.

548
00:37:34,294 --> 00:37:38,548
JEONGSUN MEDICAL CENTER

549
00:37:44,637 --> 00:37:46,639
MISSED CALLS
ASSEMBLYMAN NAM JOONG-DO

550
00:37:50,769 --> 00:37:52,729
Mom!

551
00:37:53,438 --> 00:37:55,356
Mom, are you okay?

552
00:37:57,317 --> 00:37:58,359
Did she get a CT scan?

553
00:37:58,443 --> 00:38:00,111
Isn't a cerebral contusion dangerous?

554
00:38:00,195 --> 00:38:01,780
What did they say? Does she need surgery?

555
00:38:01,863 --> 00:38:04,199
No. Thankfully,
the injuries aren't serious.

556
00:38:04,282 --> 00:38:06,743
She just needs to stay here
and rest up for a few days.

557
00:38:07,494 --> 00:38:10,246
They said she'll be awake soon,
so don't worry.

558
00:38:10,914 --> 00:38:12,123
Thank goodness.

559
00:38:14,542 --> 00:38:16,044
I just don't get it.

560
00:38:16,628 --> 00:38:17,712
She can't even drive.

561
00:38:17,796 --> 00:38:19,047
Why would she drive to Seoul?

562
00:38:22,342 --> 00:38:24,594
If something happens to her as well,

563
00:38:25,178 --> 00:38:26,429
I won't be able to go on.

564
00:38:29,224 --> 00:38:31,309
With Dad and Seung-ho gone,

565
00:38:31,392 --> 00:38:33,269
she's the only family I have left.

566
00:38:36,064 --> 00:38:37,023
Don't cry.

567
00:38:37,690 --> 00:38:39,234
She'll be fine.

568
00:38:39,818 --> 00:38:40,693
It's okay.

569
00:38:42,320 --> 00:38:43,363
It's okay.

570
00:38:50,995 --> 00:38:55,542
We have now reviewed
all the items on the agenda.

571
00:38:56,125 --> 00:38:57,377
Thank you, everyone.

572
00:38:58,002 --> 00:38:59,879
This meeting is dismissed.

573
00:39:02,131 --> 00:39:03,800
-Good work.
-Good work.

574
00:39:03,883 --> 00:39:05,260
Good work.

575
00:39:09,681 --> 00:39:12,225
-Good work.
-Let's go.

576
00:39:16,229 --> 00:39:17,856
Sir, your car is out front.

577
00:39:17,939 --> 00:39:19,399
-Assemblyman Nam.
-Okay.

578
00:39:19,482 --> 00:39:23,444
Can we talk over tea
or a meal sometime soon?

579
00:39:23,528 --> 00:39:24,654
Sure.

580
00:39:25,238 --> 00:39:26,573
By the way,

581
00:39:26,656 --> 00:39:29,242
about the criminal law amendment
you're planning to propose…

582
00:39:29,325 --> 00:39:31,661
-Yes?
-I also signed the motion,

583
00:39:31,744 --> 00:39:34,956
but it's not likely to pass
the committee's review.

584
00:39:35,957 --> 00:39:37,125
You have a plan, right?

585
00:39:37,208 --> 00:39:38,960
Yes, I'm preparing one.

586
00:39:39,544 --> 00:39:41,963
Are you going to bring it up
at our next meeting?

587
00:39:42,547 --> 00:39:43,506
Probably.

588
00:39:44,257 --> 00:39:46,676
-I'll be in touch with you…
-Hyeong-tae.

589
00:39:46,759 --> 00:39:48,052
Yes, sir.

590
00:39:48,136 --> 00:39:52,140
Look into this new bill
that Nam Joong-do is planning to propose.

591
00:39:52,223 --> 00:39:53,391
Yes, sir.

592
00:40:04,402 --> 00:40:07,363
I just don't understand Assemblyman Kang.

593
00:40:13,494 --> 00:40:14,329
What?

594
00:40:16,205 --> 00:40:19,042
Considering that you're proposing
the bill at the next meeting,

595
00:40:19,542 --> 00:40:22,003
perhaps you should have held back today.

596
00:40:24,631 --> 00:40:26,466
That would have been ideal.

597
00:40:28,259 --> 00:40:31,220
But I tried to speak as gently as I could.

598
00:40:35,058 --> 00:40:38,227
Seeing how Choi Ki-young
still hasn't gotten back to me--

599
00:40:39,270 --> 00:40:40,688
CHOI KI-YOUNG (YOUNGSAN)

600
00:40:43,483 --> 00:40:44,901
Speak of the devil.

601
00:40:46,569 --> 00:40:47,946
Hello, Mr. Choi.

602
00:40:48,446 --> 00:40:49,447
<i><font color="white">Hello, sir.</font></i>

603
00:40:50,114 --> 00:40:51,658
We were supposed to meet today.

604
00:40:51,741 --> 00:40:53,368
I'm sorry I couldn't call sooner.

605
00:40:54,202 --> 00:40:55,745
Something came up.

606
00:40:57,080 --> 00:41:00,083
I heard you and your mother-in-law
met my wife today.

607
00:41:01,167 --> 00:41:02,377
Yes.

608
00:41:02,460 --> 00:41:03,670
That's why I'm calling.

609
00:41:04,712 --> 00:41:06,422
I'm having second thoughts

610
00:41:07,590 --> 00:41:10,385
about handing over the evidence.

611
00:41:15,014 --> 00:41:17,225
May I ask what changed your mind?

612
00:41:19,811 --> 00:41:23,272
My mother-in-law had a car accident
after seeing Hye-joo.

613
00:41:26,693 --> 00:41:28,736
Please don't tell Hye-joo…

614
00:41:28,820 --> 00:41:30,655
I mean, your wife about this.

615
00:41:31,155 --> 00:41:33,241
I'm sure she's already quite shaken up.

616
00:41:35,284 --> 00:41:37,161
I understand.

617
00:41:37,245 --> 00:41:38,913
I hope Ms. Lee gets better soon.

618
00:41:39,831 --> 00:41:41,082
I'll call you again.

619
00:41:41,165 --> 00:41:42,917
<i><font color="white">Okay. Thank you.</font></i>

620
00:41:47,296 --> 00:41:49,465
He's not going to hand it over.

621
00:41:51,884 --> 00:41:52,969
One minute, sir.

622
00:42:03,271 --> 00:42:04,313
Hello, Reporter Gil Na-hui.

623
00:42:04,397 --> 00:42:06,607
Sorry for calling so late.
Have you been well?

624
00:42:06,691 --> 00:42:08,943
I wanted to ask you for a favor.

625
00:42:10,111 --> 00:42:13,781
Don't you have a correspondent
at the Sinyang Police Station?

626
00:42:14,282 --> 00:42:18,202
There was a car accident today
in Jicheong-dong, Sinyang-gu.

627
00:42:19,078 --> 00:42:21,372
I'd like to know
where the victim is hospitalized.

628
00:42:34,635 --> 00:42:36,262
Were you on the phone with Ms. Kim?

629
00:42:36,345 --> 00:42:37,305
Yes.

630
00:42:38,181 --> 00:42:41,142
She said don't worry about work
and take good care of Ms. Lee.

631
00:42:42,060 --> 00:42:43,102
I see.

632
00:42:44,479 --> 00:42:47,565
I'm so glad you got here early.

633
00:42:47,648 --> 00:42:50,234
You must have come here
straight from the headquarters.

634
00:42:50,860 --> 00:42:52,111
Thank you.

635
00:42:53,696 --> 00:42:54,822
Sure.

636
00:43:04,707 --> 00:43:08,252
Mr. Choi is having second thoughts
about handing over the evidence.

637
00:43:09,420 --> 00:43:10,505
Then what should we do?

638
00:43:10,588 --> 00:43:12,965
Seung-hee's mother knows who I am.

639
00:43:15,134 --> 00:43:16,094
Let's go on TV.

640
00:43:16,803 --> 00:43:18,096
TV?

641
00:43:18,179 --> 00:43:20,139
Let's go on TV
and tell everyone what happened.

642
00:43:23,017 --> 00:43:24,227
No way.

643
00:43:25,478 --> 00:43:26,687
I can't do that.

644
00:43:28,314 --> 00:43:29,232
We have no time.

645
00:43:30,399 --> 00:43:33,361
TV is the most effective platform
to disclose what happened.

646
00:43:34,695 --> 00:43:37,156
But whatever I say will sound less sincere

647
00:43:37,990 --> 00:43:39,867
if you're not there with me.

648
00:43:40,493 --> 00:43:42,245
After all, I'm still a third party.

649
00:43:44,372 --> 00:43:45,873
Since there was no investigation,

650
00:43:46,582 --> 00:43:49,585
there's no proof that you didn't lie.

651
00:43:51,003 --> 00:43:52,797
In order for the public to believe us,

652
00:43:53,297 --> 00:43:55,258
you have to be there yourself.

653
00:44:01,430 --> 00:44:02,932
I'll be right by your side.

654
00:44:04,559 --> 00:44:06,185
So don't be too scared.

655
00:44:11,274 --> 00:44:13,025
I'm sorry, honey.

656
00:44:13,109 --> 00:44:14,694
I can't do it.

657
00:44:15,778 --> 00:44:17,613
-Honey--
-I can't!

658
00:44:19,157 --> 00:44:20,533
I'm too scared.

659
00:44:20,616 --> 00:44:23,911
I'm scared of what might happen
after the incident comes to light.

660
00:44:23,995 --> 00:44:27,707
And you want me to talk about it on TV?

661
00:44:28,624 --> 00:44:29,500
Honey.

662
00:44:30,209 --> 00:44:31,961
I really can't do that.

663
00:44:34,380 --> 00:44:37,550
Can't you just issue a press release?

664
00:44:37,633 --> 00:44:38,634
As I said,

665
00:44:39,218 --> 00:44:42,638
we must show our sincerity
since we have no solid proof.

666
00:44:43,264 --> 00:44:45,558
And to do that,
you need to appear in public.

667
00:44:50,938 --> 00:44:52,398
Don't tell me

668
00:44:53,816 --> 00:44:57,486
you already made up your mind again
before asking me to do this.

669
00:45:01,741 --> 00:45:03,951
-Did you really?
-Hye-joo.

670
00:45:04,035 --> 00:45:06,704
You didn't mention anything
about going on TV yesterday!

671
00:45:06,787 --> 00:45:08,748
Things suddenly took a turn today.

672
00:45:10,666 --> 00:45:12,585
I didn't plan for this.

673
00:45:12,668 --> 00:45:13,961
Don't fight.

674
00:45:17,006 --> 00:45:17,840
Yoon-seo.

675
00:45:18,758 --> 00:45:21,385
Why do you guys keep fighting these days?

676
00:45:23,012 --> 00:45:25,848
Yoon-seo, we weren't fighting.

677
00:45:30,227 --> 00:45:31,354
Honey.

678
00:46:01,842 --> 00:46:02,969
You should go on TV.

679
00:46:05,388 --> 00:46:06,514
What happened back then

680
00:46:07,181 --> 00:46:09,058
wasn't your fault.

681
00:46:10,434 --> 00:46:12,144
So go on TV

682
00:46:12,853 --> 00:46:14,313
and speak up for yourself.

683
00:46:15,147 --> 00:46:17,066
Then Dad will make sure

684
00:46:17,149 --> 00:46:19,026
that the bill gets passed.

685
00:46:21,779 --> 00:46:22,697
Right, Dad?

686
00:46:22,780 --> 00:46:24,198
You will do that, right?

687
00:46:29,495 --> 00:46:30,913
Even if it gets passed,

688
00:46:30,997 --> 00:46:33,416
it won't affect your case, right?

689
00:46:35,668 --> 00:46:38,421
But if you muster up the courage
and appear on TV

690
00:46:39,213 --> 00:46:43,426
and if Dad pushes the bill
through the National Assembly,

691
00:46:44,176 --> 00:46:46,637
it'll help anyone who's going through

692
00:46:46,721 --> 00:46:48,639
the same thing as you did.

693
00:46:51,726 --> 00:46:55,855
I understand what you're worried about.

694
00:46:56,605 --> 00:46:57,648
But…

695
00:47:00,067 --> 00:47:02,319
it's inevitable for the greater good.

696
00:47:13,122 --> 00:47:14,331
Mom.

697
00:47:15,374 --> 00:47:18,961
Not only do you have Dad,
but you have me as well.

698
00:47:22,089 --> 00:47:23,382
So Mom,

699
00:47:24,800 --> 00:47:25,801
stay strong.

700
00:47:30,598 --> 00:47:31,974
I love you.

701
00:48:08,803 --> 00:48:12,181
<i><font color="white">She didn't want you
to come back to pick it up.</font></i>

702
00:48:12,264 --> 00:48:14,475
<i><font color="white">I guess she doesn't want
to see you ever again.</font></i>

703
00:48:15,601 --> 00:48:16,519
-Mom.
-Yes?

704
00:48:16,602 --> 00:48:18,813
You're being so nice
to your daughter-in-law lately.

705
00:48:18,896 --> 00:48:21,315
You used to bad-mouth her. I'm jealous.

706
00:48:21,398 --> 00:48:23,651
It's not because I like her.

707
00:48:23,734 --> 00:48:26,529
It's because she's pregnant
with my grandchild.

708
00:48:27,113 --> 00:48:29,740
I hope she doesn't have
another miscarriage.

709
00:48:30,407 --> 00:48:32,409
I want a grandchild.

710
00:48:42,586 --> 00:48:44,839
SLEEPING ROOM

